						<div class="postbody">Aha, so the background would only be lines of colour, and the sprites would provide the detail. <br />I might change this, but right now, the wall is completely opaque (the bg colour is the bright sky one, and the black is shared by three subpalettes), so that's a start. <br /><br />I'll keep this idea in the options drawer for posterity*, thanks!<br /><br /><br />*(it'll take some time before we can actually work on this properly because we already have one game to finish).<br /><br />Another (simpler, less impressive) option is to simply center the camera so nothing outside is shown when scrolling vertically. <br /><br />If blarggs' tool is accurately showing these artifacts, i don't think the still image looks that bad? I'm a bit pleased it seems to smooth out the gradient a bit. <br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
