					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Normally, the NES PPU skips one dot before every second video field in order to make the dot crawl pattern appear stable. But it doesn't skip the dot if rendering is turned off. So to get that shimmering on an NES, you could leave rendering turned off for the first scanline for two consecutive frames out of every eight, ten. This may be tricky to time and may cause (invisible) flicker artifacts in the top overscan, I'll admit.</div>

